President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Michael P. Botticelli as Deputy Director of the Office of National Drug Control Policy. Botticelli currently serves as the Director of the Bureau of Substance Abuse Services in the Massachusetts Department of Health. He has extensive experience in the field, having served in various roles within the MDPH since 1994.

Christy Romero has been nominated as the Special Inspector General for the Troubled Asset Relief Program. She is currently the Deputy Special Inspector General for SIGTARP, a position she has held since 2011. Romero previously served as Chief of Staff of SIGTARP and also worked at the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission, where she investigated financial fraud and other violations.

Alex Mehran has been appointed as a member of the Board of Directors of the Presidio Trust. He is the President and CEO of Sunset Development Company, a real estate development and management company based in California. Mehran is also involved in various other organizations, including the Contra Costa Economic Partnership and the San Francisco Ballet.

President Obama praised these individuals as dedicated and accomplished and expressed his confidence in their abilities to contribute to his administration's efforts in addressing the challenges facing America.